<MokaCard Title="Typography Components" Outlined Margin="MokaSpacingScale.Md" id="Typography">
	<ChildContent>
		<MokaHeading Level="3" Margin="MokaSpacingScale.Sm">MokaHeading</MokaHeading>
		<MokaHeading Level="1">Heading Level 1</MokaHeading>
		<MokaHeading Level="2">Heading Level 2</MokaHeading>
		<MokaHeading Level="3">Heading Level 3</MokaHeading>
		<MokaHeading Level="4">Heading Level 4</MokaHeading>
		<MokaHeading Level="5">Heading Level 5</MokaHeading>
		<MokaHeading Level="6">Heading Level 6</MokaHeading>
		<MokaHeading Level="2" Color="MokaColor.Primary">Colored Heading</MokaHeading>

		<MokaHeading Level="3" Margin="MokaSpacingScale.Md">MokaText</MokaHeading>
		<MokaText>Default paragraph text at the base font size (13px dense).</MokaText>
		<MokaText Size="MokaSize.Lg" Weight="MokaFontWeight.Semibold">Large semibold text.</MokaText>
		<MokaText Element="span" Color="MokaColor.Primary" Weight="MokaFontWeight.Bold">Bold primary span. </MokaText>
		<MokaText Element="span" Color="MokaColor.Error">Error colored text. </MokaText>
		<MokaText Element="span" Italic="true">Italic text.</MokaText>
		<MokaText Mono="true" Size="MokaSize.Sm">Monospace text for technical content.</MokaText>
		<MokaText Truncate="true" Style="max-width: 300px;">This is a very long text that will be truncated with an ellipsis because it exceeds the max-width of its container.</MokaText>
		<MokaText Transform="MokaTextTransform.Uppercase" Size="MokaSize.Xs" Weight="MokaFontWeight.Semibold">uppercase label style</MokaText>

		<MokaHeading Level="3" Margin="MokaSpacingScale.Md">MokaLabel</MokaHeading>
		<MokaLabel>Regular Label</MokaLabel>
		<MokaLabel Required="true">Required Label</MokaLabel>
		<MokaLabel Required="true" Color="MokaColor.Primary">Primary Required</MokaLabel>

		<MokaHeading Level="3" Margin="MokaSpacingScale.Md">MokaCode</MokaHeading>
		<MokaText>Use <MokaCode>MokaButton</MokaCode> for clickable actions and <MokaCode>MokaLink</MokaCode> for navigation.</MokaText>
		<MokaCode Block="true">
			public class MyComponent : MokaVisualComponentBase
			{
			protected override string RootClass => "my-component";
			}
		</MokaCode>

		<MokaHeading Level="3" Margin="MokaSpacingScale.Md">MokaLink</MokaHeading>
		<MokaLink Href="#">Default link</MokaLink> |
		<MokaLink Href="#" Underline="MokaLinkUnderline.Always">Always underlined</MokaLink> |
		<MokaLink Href="#" Underline="MokaLinkUnderline.None">No underline</MokaLink> |
		<MokaLink Href="https://github.com" External="true">External link</MokaLink>

		<MokaHeading Level="3" Margin="MokaSpacingScale.Md">MokaCaption</MokaHeading>
		<MokaCaption>Secondary text for descriptions, timestamps, and hints.</MokaCaption>
		<MokaCaption Color="MokaColor.Error">Error caption text.</MokaCaption>

		<MokaHeading Level="3" Margin="MokaSpacingScale.Md">MokaParagraph</MokaHeading>
		<MokaParagraph>This is a standard paragraph with relaxed line height and auto bottom-margin. When multiple paragraphs appear consecutively, they space themselves naturally.</MokaParagraph>
		<MokaParagraph>Second paragraph — notice the consistent spacing. This is the component you use for body content, articles, and documentation text.</MokaParagraph>
		<MokaParagraph Indent="true">This paragraph has a first-line indent, useful for traditional book-style or article formatting where visual breaks aren't needed between paragraphs.</MokaParagraph>
		<MokaParagraph Align="MokaTextAlign.Center" Color="MokaColor.Secondary">Centered secondary paragraph.</MokaParagraph>

		<MokaHeading Level="3" Margin="MokaSpacingScale.Md">MokaBlockquote</MokaHeading>
		<MokaBlockquote Citation="Moka.Red Design Philosophy">
			Every component you write must reflect a deep understanding of how Blazor actually works under the hood — not surface-level usage.
		</MokaBlockquote>
		<MokaBlockquote Filled="true" Citation="Performance Principle" Color="MokaColor.Success">
			Is this the most memory-efficient and performant way to do this in Blazor?
		</MokaBlockquote>

		<MokaHeading Level="3" Margin="MokaSpacingScale.Md">MokaKbd</MokaHeading>
		<MokaText>Press <MokaKbd>Ctrl</MokaKbd> + <MokaKbd>Shift</MokaKbd> + <MokaKbd>D</MokaKbd> to toggle diagnostics.</MokaText>
		<MokaText>Save with <MokaKbd>Ctrl</MokaKbd> + <MokaKbd>S</MokaKbd>, undo with <MokaKbd>Ctrl</MokaKbd> + <MokaKbd>Z</MokaKbd>.</MokaText>

		<MokaHeading Level="3" Margin="MokaSpacingScale.Md">MokaMark</MokaHeading>
		<MokaText>You can <MokaMark>highlight important text</MokaMark> with the default yellow tint.</MokaText>
		<MokaText>Or use semantic colors: <MokaMark Color="MokaColor.Primary">primary</MokaMark>, <MokaMark Color="MokaColor.Success">success</MokaMark>, <MokaMark Color="MokaColor.Error">error</MokaMark>, <MokaMark Color="MokaColor.Info">info</MokaMark>.</MokaText>
	</ChildContent>
</MokaCard>

